   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>Aurelius Ptolemion exegete and Aurelius Herakleianos, also called Morion, chief priest, both senators of the distinguished and most distinguished city of Oxyrhynchos, managers [l. 5] of the public bank, greet Aurelia Sintotoe, also called Aleitarion.  You have paid into the public bank of the nome for the reckoning of the month Choiak on behalf of  . . . [l. 10] in the hamlet of Taotri . . . of the current 19th year and the 18th year the sum of three thousand silver drachmas, totals 3,000.   The 19th and the 18th year [l. 15] of our Caesars Diocletian and Maximian, Augusti, and the 11th year of Constantine and Maximian, the most noble Caesars.  Pauni 1(.).</ab>
